DOC.HEADLINE: BRIEFLY : OTHER NEWS
DOC.TEXT: U.S. Treasury Yields Decline : Yields on five-year Treasury_notes fell_in Wednesday ' s auction to the lowest level since October.The high yield was 5.10 % , down from 5.19 % at the last auction Dec . 22 . It was the lowest rate since five-year notes sold for 4.81 % on Oct . 27 . The notes will carry a coupon interest_rate of 5 % , with each $ 10 # 000 in face_value selling for $ 9 # 956.40. A total of $ 12.03 billion in notes were sold_out of bids totaling $ 28.68 billion .
